                                <date calendar="Julian" notBefore="0700" notAfter="0900">possibly the early 9<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> century</date><note>The inscription is undated, and the claim of <bibl><ptr target="cic-bibl:boisselier-1963"/>: <biblScope>118</biblScope></bibl> that it dates to 889 CE must be based on some kind of confusion. Its script resembles that of the inscriptions issued by a king Vikrāntavarman in Southern Campā, which date between the first quarter and the middle of the 9th century. Some aspects of the contents too seem to agree with the inscriptions issued under this king Vikrāntavarman in Pāṇḍuraṅga and Kuṭhāra, e.g. the problematic word <foreign>draṃ</foreign>, which is found in equally problematic context in the inscription added by Vikrāntavarman on the base of the stela from the temple of Po Nagar at Nha Trang (<ref target="C0038.xml">C. 38</ref>).</note>
